        <para>
          A Value Set is a uniquely identifiable set of valid concept
          representations. A Value Set may be a simple flat list of
          concept codes drawn from a single code system, or it might be
          constituted by expressions drawn from multiple code systems (a
          code system is a system consisting of designations and
          meanings, for example LOINC, SNOMED-CT, ICD-10, or ISO 639
          Language Codes).
